The Moroccan government has been working to improve the country’s maternal health care system. In 2011, the government launched a national strategy to reduce maternal mortality. The strategy includes the provision of free prenatal care and free delivery services in public hospitals. The government has also been working to improve the quality of care in public hospitals.
